
[1]calenture

   CALENTURE, n. A violent ardent fever, incident to persons in hot
   climates, especially natives of cooler climates. It is attended with
   delirium, and one of the symptoms is, that the person affected imagines
   the sea to be a green field, and sometimes attempting to walk in it, is
   lost.
